decomposition temperature lowest temperature at which the tested package size will undergo a self accelerating
decomposition reaction this reaction will generate flammable vapors which may autoignite the length of time to
generate a decomposition reaction after the sadt has been reached or exceeded is dependent upon how much
the sadt has been exceeded and the length of time needed for the reaction exotherm heat spike from increasing
decomposition rate to initiate a rapid decomposition reaction typically sadt is inversely proportional to package
size larger packages will have a lower sadt due to smaller ratio to heat transfer area to volume of product
temperatures at or above the sadt can result in the release of hazardous decomposition products which are
thermal decomposition giving flammable and toxic products
